{
  "texts": [
    "Masuda et al. (2021) created a method, based on VAEs, that detects anomalies in point clouds without the need for supervision.",
    "The model trains to extract the distribution of the different characteristics of the given shapes using a graph-based encoder (Shen et al. 2018), then tries to reconstruct them using the FoldingNet-based decoder (Yang et al. 2018).",
    "This is completed with a spherical shape, like a grid, rather than a plane.",
    "Two distance metrics were considered, the EMD (Rubner et al. 2000) (15) and the CD (14).",
    "But because of faster convergence, the CD was preferred."
  ]
}